    slug: 'self-harm-internet-support-safe-browsing',
    title: 'Self-Harm and the Internet: Finding Support Without Triggering Content',
    category: 'Mental Health',
    excerpt: 'Young people who self-harm often turn to the internet for information and support, but the online landscape includes both genuinely helpful resources and content that can make things worse. This guide helps navigate it safely.',
    metaDescription: 'Self-harm and the internet: how to find genuine support online, recognise harmful content, help a young person who is self-harming, and access professional support.',
