    category: 'Digital Safety',
    excerpt: 'Sextortion, where criminals obtain intimate images and threaten to share them unless money or more images are provided, is a growing crisis among teenagers globally. This guide explains how it works, how to recognise it, and exactly what to do if it happens.',
    metaDescription: 'Understanding sextortion: how criminals target teenagers, what the warning signs are, and exactly what to do if your child is a victim. Practical guidance for families worldwide.',
